This paper deals with information-theoretic secrecy in a communication network, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of cooperative communication to improve secrecy, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of coding schemes, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
